Panax quinquefolium

   [8230.jpg]
    Authority   L.
      Family    Magnoliopsida:Rosidae:Apiales:Araliaceae
     Synonyms
   Common names American ginseng
      Editor
   Ecocrop code 8230

   Notes
   BRIEF DESCRIPTION A herbaceous plant reaching a height of about 30 cm.
   The flowers are greenish-yellow and borne in clusters, the fruit is a
   red berry with 1-3 seeds and the rhizome is 5-10 cm long and up to 2.5
   cm in diameter. USES The rhizome has medicinal properties. GROWING
   PERIOD Perennial. Seedling plants should be transplanted in their 1st
   or 2nd year. Roots are usually a marketable size after 5-7 years.
   COMMON NAMES American ginseng, Ginseng. FURTHER INF American ginseng is
   indigenous to the east coast region of Canada and United States. (pH
   estimated by the compiler). The expected yield of dried root is 1.7-2.5
   t/ha.

   Sources
   SOURCES (Panax quinquefolium L.)
   Roecklein J 1987 pp 282 [USE, LIG, FER, DRA, RAIN]
   Duke J 1975 pp 22 [PH, RAIN, TEMP]
   Rehm S 1991 pp 310 [USE]
   Hornok L 1992 pp 292-295 [TEMP, RAIN, LIG, FER, DRA, USE]

